snippet.textDisplay: The van culture is bigger than you think. I did an 03 caravan at one point mostly as a joke. Fiberglass is easy. I worked in a fiberglass boat shop at the time that did an aftermarket body kit for old air cooled Porsche 911s. Took a weekend to make a plug from it, make a quick and dirty mould and bam, a 911 kit fit a caravan.  Some 20$ underglow and 500$ in cheap audio and off to troll the Thursday night coffee meets
snippet.textOriginal: The van culture is bigger than you think. I did an 03 caravan at one point mostly as a joke. Fiberglass is easy.
